# API Route Conventions

## Structure

Every route handler file should follow this pattern:

1. Imports (auth, models, Zod schemas, db connection)
2. Zod validation schema(s) for request body
3. Route handler functions (GET, POST, PATCH, DELETE)

## Auth Check

```typescript
import { auth } from "@/lib/auth";

export async function GET() {
  const session = await auth();
  if (!session?.user) {
    return NextResponse.json(
      { error: { code: "UNAUTHORIZED", message: "Not authenticated" } },
      { status: 401 }
    );
  }
  // ...
}
```

## Cron Route Protection

Cron routes must verify the cron secret header:

```typescript
import { getSetting } from "@/lib/settings/service";

const cronSecret = await getSetting("security.cronSecret");
if (req.headers.get("x-cron-secret") !== cronSecret) {
  return NextResponse.json({ error: { code: "UNAUTHORIZED" } }, { status: 401 });
}
```

## Database

Use the storage adapter for all data operations:

```typescript
import { db } from "@/lib/storage";

export async function GET() {
  const store = await db();
  const groups = await store.getGroupsByAdmin(session.user.id);
  // ...
}
```
